  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance to vulnerable families affected by Hurricane Eta - Nov 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Delivery of food packages: 500 packages will be delivered to the same number of families in order to ensure food for daily consumption (rice, sugar, oil, beans, pasta, oatmeal) while the producers harvest the coffee production that managed to survive the hurricane and obtain some income to supply their basic needs. The content of the food packages has been deisgned in consultation with community members, particularly women, the elderly, and households of various sizes. 2) Delivery of COVID 19 emergency kit: In addition to the damage caused by hurricane ETA, the COVID-19 pandemic is another issue of great importance that needs to be addressed in the coffee growing areas for the current 2020-2021 harvest,</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project responds to a post-Hurricane Epoch food and health security (covid) crisis. These 5000 people are directly affected by the loss of their food and livelihood. The most affected are women, youth and children. There are 16 poor communities and the impact of this project is direct to meeting the immediate needs of these families.</narrative>
  </description>
